track_notes:
2.7 mile hike with 1280 EG and 680 EL.  Access is along seasonal FS Road 4652 (3/15-12/31) and there are several places to park alongside the road near Bald Gap (35.3616, -83.0703).  Start out on the logging road heading around the west side of Snaggy Bald - W4C/WM-016 for about 0.4 miles then head left down the slope to gain the ridgeline.  You will basically maintain the ridgeline for 2.0 before reaching the summit.  The ridgeline is the boundary of the National Forest and private property and the summit itself is on private property.  There is a trail heading south down the hill and while it is not optimal, it does provide the only space to set up in.  Lots of rhododendron and could only put up my EFHW at low elevation. There is one place along the narrow ridgeline near the summit that you have to get over a 6 boulder.

Doing Snaggy Bald as a double headed is a good idea, especially if you are parked at the bottom of it!
Planned descent track of Snaggy Bald to do Doubletop Mountain.   Follow Patricks track to ascend Snaggy Bald.
Descent and return to the parking area
